{"type":"text","value":"What Happens When You Hit a URL?"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When you type a URL, it doesn‚Äôt directly go to the router. First, the browser performs some internal operations:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ol","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cache Check"}]},{"type":"text","value":": The browser checks if the requested resource is available in its cache."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Service Workers"}]},{"type":"text","value":": If a service worker is registered, it intercepts the request and decides how to handle it. (More on this later.)"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Router Communication"}]},{"type":"text","value":": After these checks, the request is sent to the router. Some smart routers may cache resources to speed up responses."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The router then communicates with the ISP, which handles the rest of the process."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To observe how service workers and network requests work:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ol","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Open this site in your browser: "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://service-worker-stale-while-revalidate.glitch.me/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://service-worker-stale-while-revalidate.glitch.me/"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Open "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Inspect Mode"}]},{"type":"text","value":" in the browser and go to the "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Network"}]},{"type":"text","value":" tab."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Make a request and observe the timing for responses (e.g., "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"200"}]},{"type":"text","value":" for success, "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"304"}]},{"type":"text","value":" for cached responses)."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"We will discuss HTTP status codes ("},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"200"}]},{"type":"text","value":", "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"304"}]},{"type":"text","value":", etc.) and other details later, or you can explore them online."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"image.png","src":"https://heyashu.in/images/blogs/web_works_5.jpg"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"So, when you're getting data from the server, in some cases, the server does not serve the request directly. Instead, a "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"service worker"}]},{"type":"text","value":" plays a role in providing the data. Let‚Äôs look at this scenario."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"I reloaded the page and clicked on a request with a status code "},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":[]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"200"}]},{"type":"text","value":". I noticed the "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"service worker"}]},{"type":"text","value":" responded faster. It's not just about speed; the service worker also provides "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"caching"}]},{"type":"text","value":" and "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"offline support"}]},{"type":"text","value":" in the browser."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"image.png","src":"https://heyashu.in/images/blogs/web_works_6.jpg"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"service-workers"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Service Workers"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Service workers enhance the performance of requests made by the browser. Now we understand that before reaching the ISP, caching occurs, and service workers may play a role. Let‚Äôs now focus on the ISP layer."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"isp-layer"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ISP Layer"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What we currently know is that ISPs deal with the internet, but that‚Äôs not entirely true."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When you request data via an IP, it often passes through multiple layers of ISPs:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ol","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Local ISPs"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Regional ISPs"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Global ISPs"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Then, it reaches the server in the respective country."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"However, this is not always the case. Big companies like Netflix and Google optimize their systems by deploying "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"data centers"}]},{"type":"text","value":" in multiple countries. This minimizes cross-region requests and ensures faster access to data. For example, Netflix stores data at the "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"regional ISP level"}]},{"type":"text","value":", so users experience minimal latency."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To check details related to any domain, visit "},{"type":"element","tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://www.whois.com/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://www.whois.com/"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"isp-to-servers"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ISP to Servers"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Let‚Äôs discuss what happens when a request goes from the ISP to the server."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"three-way-handshake"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Three-Way Handshake"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you‚Äôve studied computer networks, you might know this already. If not, let‚Äôs review:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ol","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SYN (Synchronize)"}]},{"type":"text","value":": The client sends a synchronization request to the server."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"ACK (Acknowledge)"}]},{"type":"text","value":": The server responds, acknowledging the request."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"steps-from-isp-to-server"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Steps from ISP to Server"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ol","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"DNS Lookup"}]},{"type":"text","value":":"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"This step resolves the domain name to the correct IP address. You can learn more about DNS lookups separately. For now, think of it as finding the correct IP for the given domain name."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"TCP Handshake"}]},{"type":"text","value":":"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"Before any data transfer, the client checks the availability of the server through a "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"TCP handshake"}]},{"type":"text","value":" (SYN and ACK)."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SSL Handshake"}]},{"type":"text","value":" (for HTTPS):"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"If the URL uses HTTPS, an SSL handshake ensures encrypted communication between the client and server, enhancing security."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"HTTP GET Request"}]},{"type":"text","value":":"},{"type":"element","tag":"br","props":{},"children":[]},{"type":"text","value":"After the handshake, the browser sends the HTTP GET request, and the server responds with the requested data."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This process ensures a secure and efficient connection between the client and the server."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"image.png","src":"https://heyashu.in/images/blogs/we_works_7.jpg"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"ssl-secure-sockets-layer"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SSL: "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Secure Sockets Layer"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"An SSL handshake is "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"a series of communications between a client and a server that establishes a connection and verifies the security of both parties."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"During this process:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ol","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Certificate Exchange"}]},{"type":"text","value":": Certificates are exchanged to ensure that the communication is secure and cannot be hijacked."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Encryption"}]},{"type":"text","value":": A secure, encrypted channel is established between the client and server."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Finally, you receive "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"HTML, CSS, JS"}]},{"type":"text","value":", and other resources like images, which are rendered in the browser."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"img","props":{"alt":"image.png","src":"https://heyashu.in/images/blogs/web_works_